20 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Dolphin51", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePrisons:Erased redundant words.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom"}
{"title_page": "Joseph Dries", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n|name=\n|image= Joseph Dries 1963.jpg\n| image_size     = 240px\n|caption= Joseph Dries at the 1963 [[Olympia's Tour]]\n|birth_date={{birth-date and age|2 August 1942}}\n|birth_place=Lille (Antwerpen), Belgium\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n| height = \n| weight = \n|sport=Cycling\n|club=\n|alma_mater=\n| show-medals    = yes\n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Joseph Dries''' (born 2 August 1942) is a retired Belgian road cyclist who was active between 1962 and 1963. He won the [[Olympia's Tour]] in 1963 and one stage of [[Tour de Pologne]] in 1962.<ref name=r1/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=r1>[http://cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=8340 Joseph Dries]. cyclingarchives.com</ref>\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dries, Joseph}}\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Lille, Belgium]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp (province)]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1940s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sportsperson\n|name=\n|image= Joseph Dries 1963.jpg\n| image_size     = 240px\n|caption= Joseph Dries at the 1963 [[Olympia's Tour]]\n|birth_date={{birth-date and age|2 August 1942}}\n|birth_place=Lille (Antwerpen), Belgium\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n| height = \n| weight = \n|sport=Cycling\n|club=\n|alma_mater=\n| show-medals    = yes\n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Joseph Dries''' (born 2 August 1942) is a retired Belgian road cyclist who was active between 1962 and 1963. He won the [[Olympia's Tour]] in 1963 and one stage of [[Tour de Pologne]] in 1962.<ref name=r1/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=r1>[http://cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=8340 Joseph Dries]. cyclingarchives.com</ref>\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dries, Joseph}}\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Lille, Belgium]]\n[[