{"title_page": "Joseph Borguet", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Joseph Borguet\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1951|4|16|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Li\u00e8ge]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| proteam1       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n| updated        =\n}}\n'''Joseph Borguet''' (born 16 April 1951) is a former Belgian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. He rode the [[1979 Tour de France|1979]] and [[1980 Tour de France]].<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=2469 |title=Joseph Borguet |accessdate=4 November 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref><ref name=\"procyclingstats\">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider.php?id=167718 |title=Joseph Borguet |accessdate=4 November 2014 |work=ProCyclingStats}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|2469}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Borguet, Joseph}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Li\u00e8ge]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Joseph Borguet\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1951|4|16|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Li\u00e8ge]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| prote